description: An netmasterAlarmTrap signifies that an alarm event has arrived
from the Fault Management Module. The Alarm event can be
either due to an alarm condition in one of the network
elements being monitored by the NG-NMS or by the NG-NMS
system itself

description: Unique identifier for each alarm that is generated from
the NMS. Two similar alarms from the same NE should have
different alarmIds
variables.name: MWRM2-NMS-MIB::netmasterAlarmId

description: The System Distinguished Name (SDN) used for identifying
the source of Alarm
variables.name: MWRM2-NMS-MIB::netmasterAlarmObjectName

description: Indicates the object class (type) to which the object
instance belongs to.
variables.name: MWRM2-NMS-MIB::netmasterAlarmObjectType

description: The time of generation of the event. This is an optional
field.
variables.name: MWRM2-NMS-MIB::netmasterAlarmTimeNe

description: The time of realization of the event by the EMS
variables.name: MWRM2-NMS-MIB::netmasterAlarmTimeEms

description: True if the alarm/event represents a condition that can be
cleared at a later time (or is itself a clear);
false otherwise
variables.name: MWRM2-NMS-MIB::netmasterAlarmIsClearable

description: Defines further qualification as to the probable cause of
the alarm
variables.name: MWRM2-NMS-MIB::netmasterAlarmProbableCause

description: Defines further native qualification as to the probable cause of
the alarm
variables.name: MWRM2-NMS-MIB::netmasterAlarmNativeProbableCause

description: This parameter, when present, may further qualify the
source of the alarm
variables.name: MWRM2-NMS-MIB::netmasterAlarmProbableCauseQualifier

description: The layer to which this alarm is relevant to. This
parameter, when present, may further qualify the source
of the alarm
variables.name: MWRM2-NMS-MIB::netmasterAlarmLayer

description: Free form text description to be reported. NMS is not
required to understand the semantics of this field for
interpretation of the notification
variables.name: MWRM2-NMS-MIB::netmasterAlarmAdditionalText

description: Indication of how it is perceived that the capability of
the object has been affected
variables.name: MWRM2-NMS-MIB::netmasterAlarmPerceivedSeverity

description: The AlarmType classifies the alarm into one of the five
basic categories as specified in ITU-T X.733
variables.name: MWRM2-NMS-MIB::netmasterAlarmType

description: Indication as to whether the alarm has been acknowledged. Enumerated as TMF 3.0 AcknowledgeIndication.
variables.name: MWRM2-NMS-MIB::netmasterAlarmAcknowledgeIndication

description: Source of the alarm in a user friendly pattern
variables.name: MWRM2-NMS-MIB::netmasterAlarmResourceDisplayname

description: Originating device type

description: The name of the NE where this software is stored
variables.name: MWRM2-NMS-MIB::netmasterSWinventoryResource

description: The name of the software in this memory bank, as read from the NE.
variables.name: MWRM2-NMS-MIB::netmasterSWinventoryName

description: Software revision. Normally a five character code, but the field will display NA if the system has
this unit present but is unable to retrieve the information from it.
variables.name: MWRM2-NMS-MIB::netmasterSWinventoryVersion

description: When this software was created.
variables.name: MWRM2-NMS-MIB::netmasterSWinventoryBuildTime

description: Software location on the NE.
variables.name: MWRM2-NMS-MIB::netmasterSWinventoryMemoryBank

description: Displays the status of the memory bank and can be one of the following values
IDLE: Software is not being executed
ACTIVE: Software is being executed
ACTIVE_PENDING: Software is waiting to be executed (will be activated on next restart)
DOWNLOADING: SW is being downloaded to this bank.
ERASING FLASH: SW is being erased (during a download process)
INVALID: corrupt software or wrong software version; SW Download has failed or SW bank has not been used.
NOT_AVAILABLE: The IDU does not have contact with the unit using this software (only relevant for ODU banks) or corrupted memory bank.
variables.name: MWRM2-NMS-MIB::netmasterSWinventoryStatus
